Ctrl + A or Home 
 
Moves the cursor to the start of a line.
 

 Ctrl+ E or End 
 
Moves the cursor to the end of a line.
 

 Esc + B 
 
Moves to the beginning of the previous or current word.
 

 Ctrl + K 
 
Deletes from the current cursor position to the end of the line.
 

 Ctrl + U 
 
Deletes from the start of the line to the current cursor position.
 

 Ctrl + W 
 
Deletes the word before the cursor.
 

 Alt + B 
 
Goes back one word at a time.
 

 Alt + F  
 
Moves forward one word at a time.
 

 Alt + C 
 
Capitalizes letter where cursor is and moves to end of word.
 



--------------------- ASMI logs in HMC ---------------

1. Login to HMC.
2. System Management> Servers > select the problematic server
3. Click on Operations> Launch Advanced System Management
4. Login to ASMI, Username is 'admin' and default password is 'admin'
5. Click on System Configuration > Hardware Deconfiguration > Memory Deconfiguration > select and click on continue. 
Please share the screenshots of memory deconfiguration.
4.Click on System service aids > Error/Event logs > select all > Click on show details > Copy all the events, save it in a wordpad document and share the same with us.

-------------------- END ------------------------
